channel.title: Trying to portforward, having troubles finding my ip adress, ipconfig error?
channel.description:
i have windows xp and when i go to start, run, cmd, then type ipconfig i get this [code]Microsoft Windows XP [Version 5.1.2600] (C) Copyright 1985-2001 Microsoft Corp.
C:\Documents and Settings\william>ipconfig 'ipconfig' is not recognized as an internal or external command, operable program or batch file.
C:\Documents and Settings\william>[/code] is there a way to fix this or find my ip adress any other way?

ok this is what you do…

start>My Computer>Local Disk>WINDOWS>System32> scroll down until you find “cmd” and it has a icon of Command Prompt. open that up and then type in “ipconfig” or “ipconfig/all”
